01:59:00,920 --> 01:59:05,960
"Both the sun and the moon
rose up as the grooms."

1740
01:59:06,360 --> 01:59:10,960
"The whole earth stood petrified
at that sight."

1741
01:59:11,640 --> 01:59:16,600
"Whom does the dusk belong to?"

1742
01:59:16,920 --> 01:59:21,800
"The sun or the moon?"

1743
01:59:22,120 --> 01:59:27,040
"The idol opened its eyes"

1744
01:59:27,480 --> 01:59:31,560
"and the doors opened by itself."

1745
01:59:32,560 --> 01:59:37,680
"The dusk dressed up"

1746
01:59:38,160 --> 01:59:42,960
"as a beautiful bride."

1747
02:00:01,920 --> 02:00:04,760
You guys seem to be
worried about me.

1748
02:00:06,400 --> 02:00:08,400
I don't want you guys
to fight over me.

1749
02:00:09,120 --> 02:00:12,040
I'm also not a toy that you guys

1750
02:00:12,160 --> 02:00:14,440
can play around with.

1751
02:00:17,200 --> 02:00:19,960
At some point, both of you started
loving me for no reason.

1752
02:00:20,600 --> 02:00:22,920
Then at some stage,
you say

1753
02:00:22,960 --> 02:00:24,800
that neither of you don't want me.

1754
02:00:25,480 --> 02:00:26,920
Why are you guys like this?

1755
02:00:30,240 --> 02:00:33,480
Have I done anything to hurt you
at any point of time?

1756
02:00:34,080 --> 02:00:34,960
Tell me.

1757
02:00:36,040 --> 02:00:39,120
Hari loves Krishnan
and Krishnan loves Hari.

1758
02:00:39,360 --> 02:00:43,280
A third person has no
place in their lives.

1759
02:00:43,800 --> 02:00:45,680
I don't want to be
that third person.

1760
02:00:50,640 --> 02:00:53,840
Since we have become so close

1761
02:00:54,320 --> 02:00:58,840
I would like to be your friend.

1762
02:00:59,800 --> 02:01:01,480
Please agree to my request.

1763
02:01:06,200 --> 02:01:10,080
If you find it hard to agree,
it's okay.

1764
02:01:10,320 --> 02:01:13,960
I'm used to living alone
and can continue that way.

1765
02:01:18,760 --> 02:01:21,080
Mira shouldn't be alone in life.

1766
02:01:21,720 --> 02:01:24,560
One of us should be there for her.
- Both of us will be there for her.

1767
02:01:25,320 --> 02:01:29,560
One of us as her friend
the other as her partner.

1768
02:01:44,360 --> 02:01:46,600
You seem to have taken a decision.

1769
02:01:46,720 --> 02:01:49,200
Whom are you going to marry?

1770
02:01:49,360 --> 02:01:53,080
Nobody.
I will be their friend.

1771
02:02:00,080 --> 02:02:04,840
What is the progress? - I found the
whereabouts of the six-member gang.

1772
02:02:04,880 --> 02:02:06,080
Here is the detailed report.

1773
02:02:06,240 --> 02:02:10,320
The Sahyagiri estate barn
is their hideout.

1774
02:02:10,400 --> 02:02:11,440
They are there.

1775
02:02:12,360 --> 02:02:14,200
Mira, before you meet Mohini Varma

1776
02:02:14,680 --> 02:02:16,640
there are certain things
you should know.

1777
02:02:17,080 --> 02:02:20,640
All that glitters beautifully

1778
02:02:20,720 --> 02:02:22,880
might not be gold in reality.

1779
02:02:23,240 --> 02:02:26,040
The Mohini you wanted to meet
for all these years

1780
02:02:26,600 --> 02:02:28,200
was a lie.

1781
02:02:29,800 --> 02:02:31,240
Just like the rainbow.

1782
02:02:34,320 --> 02:02:36,200
Mohini is the person who kindled

1783
02:02:36,320 --> 02:02:39,560
a spectacular
creativity in Guptan.

1784
02:02:40,800 --> 02:02:42,960
A phenomenon that seems
true from far away.

1785
02:02:44,080 --> 02:02:47,520
Just like your grandmother
predicted

1786
02:02:48,080 --> 02:02:51,160
you will never meet Mohini Varma.

1787
02:02:52,800 --> 02:02:55,600
But you might stumble
upon its origins.

1788
02:02:56,600 --> 02:02:58,920
Anyway, you should accompany us.

1789
02:02:59,200 --> 02:03:02,440
We are going to meet
that mysterious woman.

1790
02:03:50,560 --> 02:03:52,640
We are not here to see you.

1791
02:03:52,720 --> 02:03:55,080
We are here to know about Mohini
Varma, who got Guptan killed.

1792
02:03:58,280 --> 02:03:59,480
Where is Mohini?

1793
02:04:01,200 --> 02:04:03,280
Where is Mohini?

1794
02:04:03,360 --> 02:04:04,440
Where is Mohini Varma?

1795
02:04:04,960 --> 02:04:07,560
We don't know.
- Oh, you don't?

1796
02:04:07,640 --> 02:04:10,040
Tell us where Mohini is!

1797
02:04:10,560 --> 02:04:12,240
Tell me.

1798
02:04:13,920 --> 02:04:14,920
Tell me.

1799
02:04:14,960 --> 02:04:16,920
Don't make me beat you.
Tell me.

1800
02:04:16,960 --> 02:04:18,800
Tell me, where is Mohini?

1801
02:04:18,880 --> 02:04:20,280
Tell me, where is Mohini?

1802
02:04:20,680 --> 02:04:25,720
The Mohini you are looking
for is him. Sudarsanan.

1803
02:04:38,400 --> 02:04:42,000
So you are going to
tell us what happened.

1804
02:04:42,080 --> 02:04:43,840
No. Don't ask him anything.

1805
02:04:44,040 --> 02:04:45,640
His guilt is driving him crazy.

1806
02:04:45,720 --> 02:04:48,600
We are here to stop him
from killing himself.

1807
02:04:52,040 --> 02:04:55,280
You will feel a lot better
when you talk openly.

1808
02:04:56,080 --> 02:04:58,360
Yes. I will tell you everything.

1809
02:04:58,440 --> 02:04:59,640
There is no other way.

1810
02:05:00,160 --> 02:05:03,560
Nobody killed our beloved
Mr. Guptan.

1811
02:05:04,200 --> 02:05:06,720
He committed suicide
because of me.

1812
02:05:10,240 --> 02:05:13,960
Mr. Guptan was a visiting professor
of philosophy at St. Francis.

1813
02:05:14,600 --> 02:05:16,640
We became close friends quickly.

1814
02:05:17,280 --> 02:05:21,080
He saw life as a beautiful poem.

1815
02:05:24,200 --> 02:05:25,800
When we became closer

1816
02:05:26,000 --> 02:05:29,520
we found out that he was planning
to become a saint.

1817
02:05:30,560 --> 02:05:32,520
We felt that such a person
who appreciates beauty

1818
02:05:32,680 --> 02:05:35,880
like him should enter
into wedlock.

1819
02:05:36,120 --> 02:05:39,680
When we went to his house,
his father requested the same.

1820
02:05:40,080 --> 02:05:42,800
We couldn't understand
the woman of his dreams

1821
02:05:43,000 --> 02:05:45,920
even though we tried many times.

1822
02:05:45,960 --> 02:05:49,920
That's when we asked Sudarsanan,
who used to write poems

1823
02:05:49,960 --> 02:05:54,400
to write poems as a lover to know
the feelings of Guptan.

1824
02:05:54,680 --> 02:05:57,160
We heard that he studied
in a college at Indore.

1825
02:05:57,800 --> 02:06:01,960
I created a lover,
who wrote poems for him

1826
02:06:02,240 --> 02:06:04,280
in the backdrop of the
college at Indore.

1827
02:06:04,320 --> 02:06:07,920
Then I transferred her to Delhi.

1828
02:06:08,680 --> 02:06:10,600
I gave her the name Mohini Varma.

1829
02:06:12,680 --> 02:06:16,520
As Mohini Varma,
I wrote him poems in letters.

1830
02:06:16,880 --> 02:06:20,480
He just glanced through
the first few letters.

1831
02:06:21,080 --> 02:06:25,440
But when Sudarsanan started
writing poems, he began to notice.

1832
02:06:26,080 --> 02:06:28,720
He started to admire Mohini.

1833
02:06:28,800 --> 02:06:31,080
To awaken the lover in Mr. Guptan.

1834
02:06:31,240 --> 02:06:34,600
And to get him married to a girl
in Mohini's place.

1835
02:06:34,880 --> 02:06:36,520
That's all we wanted to do.

1836
02:06:36,720 --> 02:06:39,960
He not only loved Mohini

1837
02:06:40,400 --> 02:06:43,440
but also wanted to make
her his life partner.

1838
02:06:43,960 --> 02:06:45,600
We were devastated when
we came to know this.

1839
02:06:45,680 --> 02:06:49,160
We wrote a letter inviting him
to Poonoor to know what he felt.

1840
02:06:49,280 --> 02:06:50,720
We never expected him to come.

1841
02:06:51,160 --> 02:06:54,200
All we wanted to do was to beg

1842
02:06:54,280 --> 02:06:57,120
for forgiveness at his feet.

1843
02:06:57,880 --> 02:07:01,560
We told him everything.
What happened next was unexpected.

1844
02:07:01,920 --> 02:07:06,280
After hearing all this,
he consoled us.

1845
02:07:06,840 --> 02:07:10,960
He appreciated us for creating
a magical world

1846
02:07:11,360 --> 02:07:14,920
of love for a short span
of time for him.

1847
02:07:15,400 --> 02:07:17,440
He blessed me,
touching my forehead.

1848
02:07:19,440 --> 02:07:22,400
When he said goodbye to us

1849
02:07:22,800 --> 02:07:25,400
he said he didn't wish
to come down

1850
02:07:25,880 --> 02:07:29,200
from the imaginary castles
we made for him.

1851
02:07:29,760 --> 02:07:32,640
We didn't know that
those were his last words.

1852
02:07:38,200 --> 02:07:41,000
That night, he injected himself
with poison

1853
02:07:41,320 --> 02:07:44,960
and jumped onto a pickaxe
from the upper story.

1854
02:07:45,040 --> 02:07:46,680
It's all because of me!

1855
02:07:46,800 --> 02:07:48,280
It's all because of me!

1856
02:07:48,360 --> 02:07:50,880
It was me!
- Come on. Cheer up.

1857
02:07:51,240 --> 02:07:53,280
Come on. Cheer up.

1858
02:07:54,200 --> 02:07:54,960
Come on.

1859
02:07:58,120 --> 02:08:01,960
Mira, these are magical hands
of Malayalam literature.

1860
02:08:02,960 --> 02:08:06,080
This is the hand that gave birth

1861
02:08:06,440 --> 02:08:08,400
to the poems that you admired.

1862
02:08:12,240 --> 02:08:14,680
Aren't these the hands
that created the beauty

1863
02:08:14,880 --> 02:08:16,200
that Guptan admired so much?

1864
02:08:16,840 --> 02:08:21,240
These are more gifted
than the hands of Mr. Guptan.

1865
02:08:21,560 --> 02:08:23,200
Please don't say that.

1866
02:08:23,960 --> 02:08:27,360
If these hands have anything
special about them

1867
02:08:27,960 --> 02:08:31,640
that is to have had the chance
to touch Mr. Guptan's feet.

1868
02:08:33,280 --> 02:08:34,960
Sudarsanan, where is your house?

1869
02:08:39,600 --> 02:08:41,960
He doesn't have a home.
- He is an orphan.

1870
02:08:42,040 --> 02:08:43,880
He grew up in an orphanage.

1871
02:08:46,960 --> 02:08:50,280
You may be an orphan,
but you can't escape

1872
02:08:50,360 --> 02:08:53,800
the responsibility of provoking
Guptan to commit suicide.

1873
02:08:54,600 --> 02:08:56,320
No! I won't deny it!

1874
02:08:56,520 --> 02:08:59,080
I will punish myself
for killing him.

1875
02:08:59,160 --> 02:09:01,880
That is for sure.
- A criminal has no right

1876
02:09:01,960 --> 02:09:03,760
to determine his own punishment.

1877
02:09:03,840 --> 02:09:07,840
According to the whims
of Guptan's father

1878
02:09:08,320 --> 02:09:10,760
or as per the court ruling

1879
02:09:11,320 --> 02:09:13,280
you are subject to any punishment,
Sudarsanan.

1880
02:09:13,360 --> 02:09:16,160
What are you saying?
- Sudarsanan, are you ready?

1881
02:09:16,560 --> 02:09:19,520
I'm ready. - Then stay here
until we are back.

1882
02:09:19,880 --> 02:09:21,840
Come.
- Keep an eye on them. - Okay.

1883
02:09:25,240 --> 02:09:26,040
Come.

1884
02:09:27,160 --> 02:09:29,960
No! I won't allow this.

1885
02:09:30,160 --> 02:09:32,040
Those kids have done nothing wrong.

1886
02:09:33,000 --> 02:09:34,720
Guptan did not kill himself.

1887
02:09:34,960 --> 02:09:38,000
He never possessed that
poison found in his body.

1888
02:09:40,400 --> 02:09:44,480
Are you trying to make it look
like Guptan committed suicide?

1889
02:09:46,240 --> 02:09:48,360
Guptan didn't commit suicide.

1890
02:09:49,960 --> 02:09:54,520
Yes. We have to make it look like
that to move forward in the case.

1891
02:09:56,960 --> 02:10:00,640
After meeting Sudarsanan
and the others at Poonoor

1892
02:10:01,240 --> 02:10:05,600
Guptan was poisoned
when he returned to his room.

1893
02:10:06,760 --> 02:10:07,720
Who?

1894
02:10:08,960 --> 02:10:11,880
It was Dr. Jaikumar
and his brother Premkumar.

1895
02:10:13,040 --> 02:10:15,160
The children of Ramappan,
Guptan's father's distant relative.

1896
02:10:15,600 --> 02:10:17,320
Brothers who have
a craving for crime.

1897
02:10:17,680 --> 02:10:19,480
Guptan's childhood friends.

1898
02:10:20,480 --> 02:10:22,400
The ones who were supposed
to inherit Guptan's property

1899
02:10:22,880 --> 02:10:25,840
after he becomes a saint.

1900
02:10:26,800 --> 02:10:30,480
They made liabilities worth crores
with that line of thinking.

1901
02:10:31,360 --> 02:10:34,040
When they got to know that Guptan
was about to marry Mohini Varma

1902
02:10:34,120 --> 02:10:39,280
they lost their peace of mind.

1903
02:10:39,800 --> 02:10:41,720
There shouldn't be anybody else
to inherit the property.

1904
02:10:41,840 --> 02:10:46,200
When Guptan went to Poonoor
to pick up Mohini Varma

1905
02:10:46,640 --> 02:10:50,480
they poisoned him
in his hotel room.

1906
02:10:51,080 --> 02:10:51,960
That is the truth.

1907
02:10:52,000 --> 02:10:54,000
But that is not what the court
wants to hear.

1908
02:10:54,120 --> 02:10:55,040
The court wants evidence.

1909
02:10:55,520 --> 02:10:59,480
Evidence is what
they have not left behind.

1910
02:11:00,600 --> 02:11:02,280
Does that mean
we cannot apprehend them?

1911
02:11:04,560 --> 02:11:05,440
No, we cannot.

1912
02:11:06,040 --> 02:11:07,440
This could be the first case

1913
02:11:07,520 --> 02:11:09,880
where Harikrishnans
are helpless.

1914
02:11:12,080 --> 02:11:14,400
The poison and the syringe
used to kill him

1915
02:11:15,080 --> 02:11:19,120
was a mysterious compound created
by the brilliant Dr. Jaikumar.

1916
02:11:19,840 --> 02:11:21,400
A secret concoction
of various chemicals

1917
02:11:21,640 --> 02:11:25,120
that cannot be detected
by any lab.

1918
02:11:27,160 --> 02:11:29,360
That concoction
is the only evidence we have

1919
02:11:29,520 --> 02:11:31,240
against them.

1920
02:11:32,240 --> 02:11:34,600
Until we receive any information
about that concoction

1921
02:11:35,400 --> 02:11:37,920
no matter how hard
we fight against them

1922
02:11:38,760 --> 02:11:40,720
no court will not be able
to punish them.

1923
02:11:44,320 --> 02:11:47,320
We might just have
to watch the court

1924
02:11:48,520 --> 02:11:49,400
setting them free.

1925
02:11:50,320 --> 02:11:51,480
What do we do now?

1926
02:11:51,960 --> 02:11:54,160
Yes, there is one way.

1927
02:11:54,200 --> 02:11:55,240
Just one way.

1928
02:11:55,840 --> 02:11:58,200
There should be another situation
such as the one

1929
02:11:58,280 --> 02:11:59,200
when Guptan was murdered.

1930
02:11:59,880 --> 02:12:02,240
The criminals should be forced
to repeat their crime.

1931
02:12:02,520 --> 02:12:05,560
They have to prepare
that deadly concoction again.

1932
02:12:05,840 --> 02:12:08,080
We have to apprehend them
along with that poison.

1933
02:12:08,560 --> 02:12:09,640
So?

1934
02:12:10,120 --> 02:12:11,400
We will have to bring Guptan
back to life.

1935
02:12:12,120 --> 02:12:13,120
How?

1936
02:12:14,400 --> 02:12:17,280
This plan only has a very
small chance of success.

1937
02:12:19,120 --> 02:12:20,160
Let us see how that turns out.

1938
02:12:20,760 --> 02:12:24,200
We might have to wait for years
to catch the criminals.

1939
02:12:24,920 --> 02:12:28,040
Then we might have
to close this case

1940
02:12:28,520 --> 02:12:29,920
considering the incident
to be a suicide.

1941
02:12:31,120 --> 02:12:32,280
Don't ask us any more questions.

1942
02:12:34,960 --> 02:12:36,760
You have to be at the palace
tomorrow morning.

1943
02:12:37,040 --> 02:12:38,360
I am going to inform the Lord
about it.

1944
02:12:38,680 --> 02:12:39,680
No, I will go.

1945
02:12:40,080 --> 02:12:41,320
You both be there in the morning.

1946
02:12:45,800 --> 02:12:47,800
Those boys shouldn't know about
whatever we spoke here.

1947
02:12:48,600 --> 02:12:50,280
We won't know what
they could do

1948
02:12:50,360 --> 02:12:51,880
once they get to know
about Guptan's killers.

1949
02:12:53,280 --> 02:12:54,160
Come.

1950
02:12:59,480 --> 02:13:02,560
All of you will stay
with us tonight.

1951
02:13:05,320 --> 02:13:09,200
Tomorrow, it is the tenth day
of the festival at the palace.

1952
02:13:09,640 --> 02:13:13,640
I gave Guptan's dad my word
that I would apprehend

1953
02:13:13,920 --> 02:13:15,280
the criminals on that day.

1954
02:13:16,440 --> 02:13:18,720
We will all be going to the palace
tomorrow morning.

1955
02:13:19,160 --> 02:13:19,960
Are you ready for that?

1956
02:13:20,120 --> 02:13:20,920
Yes, we are.

1957
02:13:43,640 --> 02:13:44,920
I have been waiting.

1958
02:13:45,320 --> 02:13:47,040
You don't have to introduce
yourselves.

1959
02:13:47,200 --> 02:13:48,680
He explained everything to me.

1960
02:13:49,160 --> 02:13:50,920
Harikrishnans kept their word.

1961
02:13:51,480 --> 02:13:54,080
Well, who among you is Sudarsanan?

1962
02:13:55,680 --> 02:13:57,080
Whatever happened was fate.

1963
02:13:57,520 --> 02:14:01,280
He was destined to die
at the age of 33.

1964
02:14:01,720 --> 02:14:06,320
Let me see the boy that made him
make such a move.

1965
02:14:08,560 --> 02:14:10,640
This is Sudarsanan.

1966
02:14:17,560 --> 02:14:19,040
What was all this for?

1967
02:14:19,840 --> 02:14:22,720
Why did you play such games
with my innocent child?

1968
02:14:24,280 --> 02:14:27,200
What had he done to you
that you made him force himself

1969
02:14:27,240 --> 02:14:28,960
to commit suicide?

1970
02:14:29,200 --> 02:14:30,080
Tell me.

1971
02:14:31,520 --> 02:14:34,560
Why did you kill the only person
who was supposed to perform

1972
02:14:34,640 --> 02:14:36,960
the rituals after my demise?

1973
02:14:37,280 --> 02:14:38,120
Just tell me.

1974
02:14:38,600 --> 02:14:43,280
The court can punish him
for forcing him

1975
02:14:43,480 --> 02:14:45,960
to commit suicide.
- No.

1976
02:14:46,280 --> 02:14:47,560
I don't want the court
to punish them.

1977
02:14:47,880 --> 02:14:49,840
He deserves a punishment
that comes from the heart

1978
02:14:49,920 --> 02:14:53,720
of a father that lost
his only son.

1979
02:14:54,160 --> 02:14:55,240
Do you agree?

1980
02:14:56,280 --> 02:14:57,200
Yes, I do.

1981
02:14:57,840 --> 02:14:59,480
Then I have decided
the punishment.

1982
02:14:59,880 --> 02:15:01,560
For making me lose my son

1983
02:15:01,840 --> 02:15:06,120
he will have to stay here
and look after me and the house

1984
02:15:06,280 --> 02:15:07,200
all his life.

1985
02:15:14,840 --> 02:15:18,600
But don't think that you will get
any bit of our property.

1986
02:15:19,480 --> 02:15:21,400
I have decided what to do
with the property.

1987
